name: subatomic compressed tesselium bracelets
description: As the name implies, I took the tesselium bracelet and squished it. Quite the transformation!

name: subatomic spherium bracelets
description: At first glance this design might look like soap bubbles or maybe seed pods, but actually I got the idea from one of Andy Goldsworthy's amazing snow & ice sculptures. Named spherium for obvious reasons, the "ium" is a leftover from when my logo was a Periodic Table of the Elements, with earrings substituting for sodium, magnesium, etc.

name: subatomic tesselium bracelets
description: The name derives from "tessellation" or the repetitive patterns seen on tiled floors, wallpaper and quilts. This bracelet is an elliptical torus (or donut shape) perforated with elliptical holes.

name: spherium bracelet
description: At first glance this design might look like soap bubbles or maybe seed pods, but actually I got the idea from one of Andy Goldsworthy's amazing snow & ice sculptures. Named spherium for obvious reasons, the "ium" is a leftover from when my logo was a Periodic Table of the Elements, with earrings substituting for sodium, magnesium, etc.

name: ovoidium bracelet
description: Have you heard the one that goes: "What happens when you pull a spherium bracelet vertically?" This is the answer.

name: tesselium bracelet
description: The name derives from "tessellation" or the repetitive patterns seen on tiled floors, wallpaper and quilts. This bracelet is an elliptical torus (or donut shape) perforated with elliptical holes.

name: compressed tesselium bracelet
description: As the name implies, I took the tesselium bracelet and squished it. Quite the transformation!

name: rigatonium bracelet
description: Based on a hollow torus (donut shape) sliced like a bagel, rigatonium is one of my elbow macaroni series. An example of a design that turned out not at all like I planned... but much better!
